{"/service/ndnp/ndhi/batch_ndhi_jemhadar_ver01/data/sn85042243/00383346162/1937100601/0316.xml":{"full_text":"Eoonomist Flynn Warn* Against\nAccepting 'Recovery' at\nIts Fact Value\nit \u2022ywilnr\nout tt tin\nWhy ahoold not continued \u00abpen4\nfet brine abmit eon tinned ta\nyroremant of the Industrial \u00abt\nInk? Thla to the vmttta\n\u2022ni'nrl\nby John T- flynn, funM\nwriter on eeoR\u00abnie topic* in hit\n\u2022ertoc oo MORE ABOUT TAXES.\nBy JOHN T. iXYNN\n(Copyright, 1037, NBA Servioe, inc.)\nWit have now seen that the govern\nmeat hu paid out billions of dolltrs\nin recovery \u00bbnd relief expenditure* to\nmillions of people who ere customers\nof our business men and that all of\nthese billions have thus promptly mads\ntheir way into business. We ha^e\nattn also that the government has\nobtained all of these billions by bor\nrowing them at the banks.\nNow we can see what the effects of\nthis have been.\nFirst, it is perfectly obvious that\nthis has produced a powerful lift in\nbusiness. Men have gone back to\nwork and they in turn, drawing wages,\nspend tho\u00abe wafes with the merchants.\nAnd the profits of business have re\nturned.\nSecond, certain psychological results\nhave taken place. One is that the\ngreat majority of people accept this\nall at its face value and say flatly that\nwe have recovered. This creates con'\nfidence in their minds and puts them\nin a spending mood.\nNext, a large number of more ob\nserving people have concluded that\nthis Immense infusion of government\ncredit is the prelude to a considerable\ninflation. They believe that the forces\nmaking for inflation once set in motion\nare too powerful to be easily or qucik\nly checked. If inflation comes they\nbelieve, rightly, that prices will go up,\nwages will go up and that, therefore,\nthe value of the dollar will be reduced.\nThis makes them hesitant about lend\ning money. Instead it encourages\nthem to put their money into stocks\n\u2014equities which have a better chance\nto rise with the inflation. 'This hu\ncreated a very large demand for so\ncalled good stocks.\n\"Biggest\" Boom Predicted\nThe President's money policies have\nproduced the same effect. The Presi\ndent has devalued the dollar, cutting\ndown its gold content by 40 per cent.\nMany economists and many investors\nSchil\nllfl\n10E\nS\nbas\nmore\nflavor\nbecause\nit's\ntoasted\nrtntf\nthe bell,\nSpectre of Taxation, to Finance\nUnavoidable Spending Brakes Boom\nThe stock exchange reflects fluctuating attitudes of the country\nabout the business outlook in terms of securities prices.\nbelieve this is an inevitable force\npressing toward inflation. It has re\nsulted In the Influx of PTVE BILLION\nDOLLARS in gold, another energy\nworking for inflation.\nThen there was, beginning in Sep\ntember, 1986, a very influenzal school\nof financiers and economists who de\ncided that the mending program, plus\nthe governments resolution to avoid\ntaxing as much as possible, plus the\ngovernment's borrowing policies which\nrequired an easy money market would\nhave three effects:\n1. That we could be assured of\neasy money for some years.\n3. That the government spending\nhad primed the pump of business and\nthat we were about to see a tremend\nous expansion of the heavy construc\ntion industries.\nS. That great shortsges have piled\nup in houses, commercial building,\nplant machinery, railroad equipment,\nNation to Get Jobless\nQuiz Blanks Nov. 16\n9. 0P)\nWashington, Oct.\nThe\ncream-colored unemployment census\nquestionnaires were made public\nWednesday. On one side are 14 In\nquiries, and on the other is this state\nment by President Roosevelt:\n'If you are unemployed or partly\nunemployed and are able to Work and\nare seeking work, please fill out this\nreport card right away and mall it\nIt tPILEKY INHERITED?\nCAN IT BE CURED\nA booklet rnfUI\u00bbl\u00abI th\u00ab opinions\nmown\nALOHA\nOLD QUAK-SICS mil\u2014\nIt\nBecauat \u00ab\u00abch drop it altof, Ud\n\u2022ad sallow\nIt', two